Search
public static enum Search.SearchType
extends java.lang.Enum<Search.SearchType>

List of different types of searches that can be performed. Most involve processing combinations of vectors in different ways, in building a query expression, scoring candidates against these query expressions, or both. Most options here correspond directly to a particular subclass of VectorSearcher

See Also:
VectorSearcher

Enum Constant Summary
CONVOLUTION
          Similar to TENSOR, product similarity that trains by taking ordered pairs of terms, a target query term, and searches for the term whose convolution product with the target term gives the largest similarity with training convolution.
MAXSIM
          "Closest disjunction" - get vectors for each query term, score by measuring distance to each term and taking the minimum.
PRINTQUERY
          Build an additive query vector (as with SUM and print out the query vector for debugging.
SPARSESUM
          Build a query as with SUM option, but quantize to sparse vectors before taking scalar product at search time.
SUBSPACE
          "Quantum disjunction" - get vectors for each query term, create a representation for the subspace spanned by these vectors, and score by measuring cosine similarity with this subspace.
SUM
          Default option - build a query by adding together (weighted) vectors for each of the query terms, and search using cosine similarity.
TENSOR
          A product similarity that trains by taking ordered pairs of terms, a target query term, and searches for the term whose tensor product with the target term gives the largest similarity with training tensor.

Enum Constant Detail

SUM

public static final Search.SearchType SUM
Default option - build a query by adding together (weighted) vectors for each of the query terms, and search using cosine similarity.

See Also:
VectorSearcher.VectorSearcherCosine

SPARSESUM

public static final Search.SearchType SPARSESUM
Build a query as with SUM option, but quantize to sparse vectors before taking scalar product at search time. This can be used to give a guide to how much smilarities are changed by only using the most significant coordinates of a vector.

See Also:
VectorSearcher.VectorSearcherCosineSparse

SUBSPACE

public static final Search.SearchType SUBSPACE
"Quantum disjunction" - get vectors for each query term, create a representation for the subspace spanned by these vectors, and score by measuring cosine similarity with this subspace.

See Also:
VectorSearcher.VectorSearcherSubspaceSim

MAXSIM

public static final Search.SearchType MAXSIM
"Closest disjunction" - get vectors for each query term, score by measuring distance to each term and taking the minimum.

See Also:
VectorSearcher.VectorSearcherMaxSim

TENSOR

public static final Search.SearchType TENSOR
A product similarity that trains by taking ordered pairs of terms, a target query term, and searches for the term whose tensor product with the target term gives the largest similarity with training tensor.

See Also:
VectorSearcher.VectorSearcherTensorSim

CONVOLUTION

public static final Search.SearchType CONVOLUTION
Similar to TENSOR, product similarity that trains by taking ordered pairs of terms, a target query term, and searches for the term whose convolution product with the target term gives the largest similarity with training convolution.

See Also:
VectorSearcher.VectorSearcherConvolutionSim
